EOP persistence-prediction external-validation reference
========================================================

eop_prediction_reference.csv holds the persistence UT1 prediction-error
statistics (RMS, median, 95th-percentile, max residual) at the final-floor and
1/2/3/5/10-day horizons, computed by an INDEPENDENT NumPy re-implementation over
the same verbatim IERS finals2000A rows that Kshana's
`frame_eop::prediction_error_vs_horizon` reads. It is used to externally validate
that Rust function (see tests/validate_p4_eop_prediction_growth_longspan.rs and
tests/validate_p4_table2_horizon_longspan.rs). These files are not part of the
Kshana source and are not shipped in the published crates/packages — they exist
only for the test suite.

Oracle
------
An independent NumPy re-implementation (generate_eop_prediction_reference.py) of
the persistence prediction-error definitions. It re-parses the fixed-width
finals2000A columns with Python string slicing and recomputes the RMS and
nearest-rank percentiles with NumPy on a separate code path, in a different
language, from Kshana's Rust. Because the persistence-error statistics are a
deterministic function of the parsed daily UT1 series, matching the NumPy output
byte-for-byte (to <1e-6 s) is a genuine cross-check of Kshana's column parsing,
day-apart sample pairing, RMS reduction and percentile rule — not a
self-consistency check.

The DATA is real. The input rows are lifted byte-for-byte from the official IERS
finals2000A.all product (see the fixture header in
tests/fixtures/agency/eop/finals2000A_2022001_longspan.txt for the source URL and
MJD span), so the recovered final floor (~0.019 ms, inside the IERS-published
Bulletin A/B accuracy band ~0.01-0.02 ms) and the multi-day growth are measured
quantities. The CHOICE of persistence as the predictor is the honestly-Modelled
part: Kshana does not reproduce IERS's operational least-squares/AR Bulletin A
prediction algorithm, so the multi-day RMS bounds the achievable error rather
than reproducing the exact operational Bulletin A prediction accuracy.

Definitions (identical to src/frame_eop.rs)
-------------------------------------------
  truth(day)  = final Bulletin B UT1-UTC if present, else rapid Bulletin A UT1-UTC.
  horizon=final : |rapid Bulletin A - final Bulletin B| over every paired row.
  horizon=d<h>  : |truth(t) - truth(t+h)| for every pair of days exactly h apart
                  on the integer-MJD grid (persistence predictor UT1(t+h)=UT1(t)).
  rms_s  = sqrt(mean(resid^2))
  p50_s  = nearest-rank 50th pct of |resid| (rank = ceil(0.50*n), 1-indexed)
  p95_s  = nearest-rank 95th pct of |resid| (rank = ceil(0.95*n), 1-indexed)
  max_s  = max(|resid|)

Provenance / reproducibility
----------------------------
Generated by the committed generate_eop_prediction_reference.py over the
committed fixture tests/fixtures/agency/eop/finals2000A_2022001_longspan.txt
(45 consecutive daily rows, MJD 59578..59622, verbatim IERS finals2000A). Run:

    python3 generate_eop_prediction_reference.py \
        ../agency/eop/finals2000A_2022001_longspan.txt > eop_prediction_reference.csv

Committed CSV produced with Python 3 + NumPy 2.0.2. All *_s columns are in
SECONDS, emitted at 17 significant digits (round-trips IEEE-754 f64 exactly).

Format
------
eop_prediction_reference.csv: '#'-prefixed comment lines, then a header line, then
one row per horizon:
  horizon ; n ; rms_s ; p50_s ; p95_s ; max_s
